{
  "message": "chore(deps): update react 19.2.4, @types/node 24, document eslint 10 skip\n\nDependency updates performed via bun:\n\n- react: 19.2.3 \u2192 19.2.4 (patch \u2014 security hardening for Server\n  Actions/Components, no breaking changes)\n- react-dom: 19.2.3 \u2192 19.2.4 (same release train as react)\n- @types/node: 20.19.33 \u2192 24.10.12 (align type declarations with the\n  actual Node.js v24.12.0 runtime; the v20 types were a leftover mismatch\n  that could mask API surface differences)\n\nSkipped:\n- eslint: 9.39.2 \u2192 10.0.0 \u2014 rolled back because eslint-plugin-react\n  (transitive via eslint-config-next) calls the removed `getFilename()` API,\n  producing `TypeError: contextOrFilename.getFilename is not a function`.\n  Tracked upstream at jsx-eslint/eslint-plugin-react#3970. Will retry once\n  the plugin ships ESLint 10 compatibility.\n\nUPGRADE_LOG.md rewritten from stub to document all three updates and the\neslint skip with error details and tracking link.\n\nVerified: bun tsc --noEmit clean, bun lint clean, bun run build succeeds.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
